<div id="review_4060880757" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4060880757" />
    <a title="Herschel Chaiet" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/81826704-herschel-chaiet"><img alt="Herschel Chaiet" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4060880757?book_show_action=true">Jul 05, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Herschel Chaiet" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Herschel Chaiet" href="/user/show/81826704-herschel-chaiet">Herschel Chaiet</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4060880757" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6722242903881962629">I enjoyed listening to this as an audiobook. It was a smooth read (listen?), thorough, and balanced. It is not a polemic. <br/><br/>The thesis is rather simple: corporations have a legal obligation to pursue only profit. Any other value must legally be subordinated to profit. This results in the widespread immoral, greedy, manipulative and even criminal activities undertaken by corporations. The corporation is legally constructed to be a kind of psychopath with only one interest - profit. Corporate social</span>
  <span id="freeText6722242903881962629" style="display:none">I enjoyed listening to this as an audiobook. It was a smooth read (listen?), thorough, and balanced. It is not a polemic. <br /><br />The thesis is rather simple: corporations have a legal obligation to pursue only profit. Any other value must legally be subordinated to profit. This results in the widespread immoral, greedy, manipulative and even criminal activities undertaken by corporations. The corporation is legally constructed to be a kind of psychopath with only one interest - profit. Corporate social responsibility is only permissible when socially responsible actions further profit.<br /><br />The legal lens employed by the book allows for a more hopeful and practical solution. Controlling corporate misbehaviour is legally fixable. It does not require a revolution.<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="6722242903881962629" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


